snippet.textDisplay: While I liked the original movie IT,  i always wondered:  most of the adult Losers are rich, so why did they show up in Derry alone?  Why not hire private investigators,  professional bodyguards,   paranormal investigators, etc. and descend on the town ready to kick butt and take names?  But no they all show up alone,  emotionally compromised and physically vulnerable.   they carry on like they are still helpless kids with no support.  Rich adults can get all the backup they want.  And no one is going to care if they think you are eccentric or even crazy, if you are rich and paying them a lot of money.  So instead of a bunch of out of condition middle aged people seeking into a sewer all alone and unarmed to face a monster, you could go down accompanied by a privately hired version of Mulder and Scully, Dr. Strange,  and Seal Team 7!!    The mystical power of true love and friendship is great,  but let us not forget the true and lasting power of money!
